comments.body:
Thanks [~cheersyang] for the review.
{quote}
In ActivityManager, the changes you've done for {{startAppAllocationRecording}}, this seems to have changed the behavior, is it on purpose? 
{quote}
Updates in ActivityManager#startAppAllocationRecording won't change the behavior, only adjust the logic from "if(A&B)\{...\} if(A&!B)\{...\}" to "if(A)\{if(B)\{...\}else\{...\}\}", the purpose is to enhance the efficiency through reducing unnecessary check.

Reviewing this logic, I think there is still a race condition risk to call Map#get after Map#containsKey. I will update this logic as follows:
{code:java}
    Long turnOffTimestamp =
        recordingAppActivitiesUntilSpecifiedTime.get(applicationId);
    if (turnOffTimestamp != null) {
      if (turnOffTimestamp > currTS) {
        appsAllocation.get().put(applicationId,
            new AppAllocation(application.getPriority(), nodeID,
                application.getQueueName()));
      } else {
        turnOffActivityMonitoringForApp(applicationId);
      }
    }
{code}

